i would like to be your next senator,'' kerrey said in starting a two-day swing through the state. ``i can promise you i will never betray you. and i will never dishonor the respect i have for you.''
kerrey, 44, ended months of speculation last november when he said he would run for the senate. he has been criss-crossing nebraska since then, saying his main issues are trade policy, the federal budget, education and agriculture
a great and glorious future will not happen unless we do the unglamorous work today,'' he said
no other democrat has filed for the nomination. sen. david karnes, appointed to succeed the late democratic sen. edward zorinsky, and rep. hal daub are seeking the gop nomination
