a medal of honor winner who lost part of his right leg while serving with the navy in the vietnam war, kerrey was a popular governor in mostly republican nebraska. he made headlines for his romance with actress debra winger, who visited nebraska frequently but later married actor timothy hutton
kerrey's announcement in october 1985 that he wouldn't seek a second term shocked many nebraskans, but kerrey said it was ``time to move on.''
since leaving office, he has been involved in various business ventures, including a restaurant chain and an investment banking firm
