the dead skier was identified as maj. hugh lindsay, 34, a former aide to queen elizabeth ii, the prince's mother. buckingham palace said another skiier, patricia palmer-tomkinson, suffered leg injuries
charles' wife, diana, and pregnant sister-in-law, sarah, the duchess of york, were safe in a chalet at the time of the avalanche, said the palace statement issued in london
nasa officials warned congress on thursday that the space station program would be destroyed if money is diverted to build an unmanned scientific and manufacturing facility in space
at the same time, the space station budget came under attack elsewhere in the capitol, when rep. edward p. boland, d-mass., pressed for more money for housing programs next year and said if that money is not allocated, then congress will ``kiss goodbye to the space station.''
boland, whose house appropriations subcommittee handles funding for housing programs as well as independent agencies including the national aeronautics and space administration, said his panel would take money for housing from the budgets for nasa and the national science foundation unless congress changes the overall budget priorities
a pact allowing japan to retrieve plutonium from u.s. nuclear wastes would leave the united states without ``effective control'' over reprocessing of the hazardous material, the general accounting office has concluded
the gao, the investigative arm of congress, also found fault with the agreement's provisions to guard against proliferation of plutonium, the principal element in nuclear weapons, and said it deprived congress of its ``oversight function.''
opponents of the accord said they had failed to work out a compromise with the state department and may move to kill the agreement next week
the accord, signed in november, gives japan advance permission for 30 years to recover plutonium from the fuel the united states supplies for its nuclear power plants after it is used
