grain and soybean futures prices opened mixed today on the chicago board of trade, with soybeans posting some surprising gains in early trading
market analysts had expected soybeans to open lower on ideas that soybean plantings were on the rise and in response to an increase in the agriculture department's estimate of this year's ending stocks
instead, soybean futures were as much as 3 cents a bushel higher in early trading
it's a little bit of a surprise that some buying came into the soybean market but i don't think it's anything too significant because the market's starting to back off already,'' ted mao, grain specialist for shearson lehman hutton inc., said about a half-hour after the opening
wheat futures were steady to slightly higher. corn prices were mostly lower
