italian investor carlo de benedetti, who is vying for control of belgium's biggest holding company, thursday called for an extraordinary meeting of the shareholders of societe generale de belgique s.a
de benedetti said he would ask the meeting to consider himself and two of his belgian allies, andre leysen of gevaert n.v and pierre scohier of copeba s.a, as company directors
de benedetti and an array of belgian and international partners claim to control over 47 percent of the company's 28.2 million shares
a franco-belgian alliance is fighting de benedetti's bid to get control of societe generale and claims a majority stake of 52 percent
the group formed around belgium's biggest insurer, group ag, and the french investment firm companie financiere de suez, has also said it would like a shareholders meeting to discuss the company's future but has not called for a specific date
in addition, it stressed it is willing to talk with de benedetti, but only on the condition that the italian admits he does not have control of the company
while the uncertainty on the corporate battle continued, suez president renaud de la geniere said the fight ``could take months perhaps, but i hope i will not take years.''
de la geniere had talks with caretaker prime minister wilfried martens on the takeover bid, but no details were available
in a statement released by his french investment company cerus s.a, de benedetti said the shareholders meeting should discuss how many directors should run the company, which controls a third of the belgian economy
any shareholder with at least 20 percent of the share capital is able to convene such a meeting according to belgian commercial law
the stakes each side holds could change dramatically since a brussels court approved a capital increase of 12 million shares for societe generale. both camps claim they are entitled to the new stock. a higher court still has to rule on the increase
to sidestep the issue, de benedetti announced a request would be made at the meeting that the company not make use of its recent capital increase
leysen said de la geniere had made similar suggestions earlier and said the two sides might agree to annul the capital increase
the shares were issued by societe generale immediately after it was aware of de benedetti's intentions, which it considers hostile. the increase would dilute the stakes each side currently holds
de benedetti wants to turn the 166-year-old company into a holding company for enterprises across europe, anticipating 1992, when the movement of goods, capital and people should be free throughout the 12-nation european economic community
the alliance fighting de benedetti wants the company to remained focused in belgium. resources, inc.</head>
southdown inc., a cement and energy company, says it is increasing its tender offer for moore mccormack resources inc. to $35 per share of common stock from its previous offer of $31 per share
the increase was estimated to raise the total value of the takeover to about $450 million from a previous estimate of roughly $395 million, including offers for moore mccormack preferred stock and subordinated debt, southdown officials said thursday
we will consider this development in due course,'' said tony doumlele, director of corporate relations for moore mccormack
on march 23, southdown announced its initial cash tender offer for the stamford, conn.-based oil and gas and building materials company. at the time, moore mccormack officials called th offer ``totally unsolicited,'' but said they would study it
we haven't heard anything more (from moore mccormack management),'' said ruth pachman, spokeswoman for southdown
southdown said its tender offer is conditional upon the valid tender of a majority of moore mccormack common stock, the invalidation of moore mccormack's ``poison pill'' anti-takeover defense and the acquisition of sufficient financing
southdown said it was confident it could obtain the necessary financing to cover the tender offer and related costs
southdown produces and sells cement and ready-mixed concrete and is active in oil and gas production. moore mccormack produces building materials and is involved in oil and gas exploration and production, mainly in texas and louisiana
